JOHANNESBURG – Cup action will be the focus of South African football this weekend, as the Telkom Knockout quarterfinals take centre stage. The last-16 stage of the tournament produced 16 goal and three penalty shootouts. The quarterfinal battles kick-off with previous winners of this competition, Platinum Stars and Bloemfontein Celtic, at Royal Bafokeng Stadium on Saturday. More action follows on Saturday night with two matches at. READ: Chippa delivers knockout Sundowns blow League champions Bidvest Wits host an in-form Baroka FC side, while Orlando Pirates take on Polokwane City at Orlando Stadium. On Sunday, Chippa United welcome Kaizer Chiefs to the Nelson Mandela Bay Stadium. African News Agency